[3] Iowa (Hamilton County): commercial turkey
Date: Tue 5 Apr 2022
Source: Des Moines Register [edited]
https://bit.ly/3DXi1rd


The Iowa Department of Agriculture reported its 15th outbreak of bird flu this week, this time in a Hamilton County commercial turkey facility where 8000 birds were destroyed to prevent the spread of the highly contagious and deadly disease. It's the 2nd outbreak in the north-central Iowa county. The 1st was a week ago, when a facility with 28 000 turkeys was infected.

[byline: Donnelle Eller]

