[4] Iowa (Hardin County): commercial turkey
Date: Wed 6 Apr 2022 16:32 EDT
Source: KCRG [edited]
https://www.kcrg.com/2022/04/06/commercial-turkey-flock-catches-bird-flu-hardin-county/


Just a day after the Iowa Department of Agriculture announced another positive case of bird flu, Hardin County also confirmed a positive case of the virus. This brings the total of cases in the state from 15 to now 16, with a commercial turkey flock reportedly being the site of highly pathogenic avian influenza (HPAI).

Officials are reminding flock owners to prevent contact between their birds and wild birds, and to report sick birds or unusual deaths to the state.

Commercial and backyard HPAI detections in Iowa are as follows:
1 Mar 2022 - Pottawattamie: backyard mixed species
6 Mar 2022 - Buena Vista: commercial turkey
10 Mar 2022 - Taylor: commercial layer chickens
17 Mar 2022 - Buena Vista: commercial layer chickens
20 Mar 2022 - Warren: backyard mixed species
23 Mar 2022 - Buena Vista: commercial turkey
25 Mar 2022 - Franklin: commercial pullet chickens
28 Mar 2022 - Hamilton: commercial turkey
28 Mar 2022 - Guthrie: commercial layer chickens
29 Mar 2022 - Buena Vista: commercial turkey
31 Mar 2022 - Osceola: commercial layer chickens
31 Mar 2022 - Cherokee: commercial turkey
2 Apr 2022 - Sac: commercial turkey
2 Apr 2022 - Humboldt: commercial breeding chickens
4 Apr 2022 - Hamilton: commercial turkey
5 Apr 2022 - Hardin: commercial turkey

