[In an article from Ontario, Canada, the comment was made regarding everything we do is to protect our birds. This is absolutely correct. Every thing you do related to your birds matters. Every step, every action must be deliberate with security for your birds foremost in your mind.

This virus is wreaking disaster on every aspect of the avian industry. It has touched the commercial producers as well as the backyard grower and the hobbyist with only a few birds. If you have birds as pets, be aware because this virus does not discriminate; bring your pets inside and do not visit anyone having pet or commercial birds.

Biosecurity is the watchword of every hobbyist, backyard producer, and commercial producer. This serious virus should cause all of us to think, breathe and act with the safety of our birds and others' birds uppermost in our minds and actions. - Mod.TG

